column5: Nice perch! I'll be there all weekend
Way to go Bud!  Please tell me you're not calling that a 'livewell'
Nice man we were In that mess of boats got some and a couple slobs too
Nice haul! I was out with my pops yesterday but only managed a few small ones. Hoping to get out early next week:)
Nice Dave....and great weather to boot..

Thanks Guys I'd like to get back out, maybe next week.  â€‹ Your right Roy. Fish storage box, water was 48 that day on the surface. Ended with 71 keepers. 13.25" was the biggest. Buddy that was with me was blown away, couldn't believe the fishing and the amount of boats.  Gota get down this way Bro.  Didn't get out to the group, found a school just in from you guys.  I move around with the Electric slowly till we see the school on the bottom then anchor. Sometimes they move a pit, Just have to move 100" or so till you get on them again. I find you have to use the zoom on your finder to see them, very close to the bottom. If you see a red Princecraft with a 50 Honda Tiller just come over and anchor close say hi. There's lots out there for everyone.  Should try and get out Phil, Old Pete was with me that day. I guess Murray is going up with Andy & John in June. Wish I was going with the boys. One of these years
Great job Dave!!! Good haul   Bet cleaning those beauties took longer then putting them into your livewell eh   That's enough for a good feed
